{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":731,"text":"Miranda Wang: We're here\nto talk about accidents."},{"time":3195,"text":"How do you feel about accidents?"},{"time":5627,"text":"When we think about accidents,"},{"time":7221,"text":"we usually consider them to be harmful,"},{"time":9412,"text":"unfortunate or even dangerous,\nand they certainly can be."},{"time":13739,"text":"But are they always that bad?"},{"time":16029,"text":"The discovery that had led\nto penicillin, for example,"},{"time":18672,"text":"is one of the most fortunate\naccidents of all time."},{"time":22109,"text":"Without biologist Alexander\nFleming's moldy accident,"},{"time":25796,"text":"caused by a neglected workstation,"},{"time":27924,"text":"we wouldn't be able to fight\noff so many bacterial infections."},{"time":32276,"text":"Jeanny Yao: Miranda and I are here today"},{"time":34205,"text":"because we'd like to share\nhow our accidents"},{"time":36445,"text":"have led to discoveries."},{"time":38605,"text":"In 2011, we visited the Vancouver\nWaste Transfer Station"},{"time":42133,"text":"and saw an enormous pit of plastic waste."},{"time":45642,"text":"We realized that when\nplastics get to the dump,"},{"time":48007,"text":"it's difficult to sort them\nbecause they have similar densities,"},{"time":51363,"text":"and when they're mixed with organic matter"},{"time":53387,"text":"and construction debris,\nit's truly impossible"},{"time":55735,"text":"to pick them out and environmentally\neliminate them."},{"time":58789,"text":"MW: However, plastics are useful"},{"time":61229,"text":"because they're durable, flexible,"},{"time":63341,"text":"and can be easily molded\ninto so many useful shapes."},{"time":66613,"text":"The downside of this convenience"},{"time":68669,"text":"is that there's a high cost to this."},{"time":71078,"text":"Plastics cause serious problems, such as"},{"time":73318,"text":"the destruction of ecosystems,"},{"time":75509,"text":"the pollution of natural resources,"},{"time":77200,"text":"and the reduction of available land space."},{"time":79945,"text":"This picture you see here\nis the Great Pacific Gyre."},{"time":82589,"text":"When you think about plastic pollution"},{"time":84894,"text":"and the marine environment,"},{"time":86214,"text":"we think about the Great Pacific Gyre,"},{"time":88048,"text":"which is supposed to be a floating\nisland of plastic waste."},{"time":91237,"text":"But that's no longer an accurate depiction"},{"time":93480,"text":"of plastic pollution\nin the marine environment."},{"time":96461,"text":"Right now, the ocean is actually\na soup of plastic debris,"},{"time":100172,"text":"and there's nowhere you\ncan go in the ocean"},{"time":102445,"text":"where you wouldn't be able\nto find plastic particles."},{"time":105936,"text":"JY: In a plastic-dependent society,"},{"time":108105,"text":"cutting down production is a good\ngoal, but it's not enough."},{"time":111084,"text":"And what about the waste\nthat's already been produced?"},{"time":114325,"text":"Plastics take hundreds to thousands\nof years to biodegrade."},{"time":118053,"text":"So we thought, you know what?"},{"time":119666,"text":"Instead of waiting for that garbage\nto sit there and pile up,"},{"time":123072,"text":"let's find a way to break them down"},{"time":125488,"text":"with bacteria."},{"time":127546,"text":"Sounds cool, right?"},{"time":129180,"text":"Audience: Yeah. JY: Thank you."},{"time":130971,"text":"But we had a problem."},{"time":132293,"text":"You see, plastics have\nvery complex structures"},{"time":135997,"text":"and are difficult to biodegrade."},{"time":138141,"text":"Anyhow, we were curious and hopeful"},{"time":140322,"text":"and still wanted to give it a go."},{"time":141942,"text":"MW: With this idea in mind,\nJeanny and I read through"},{"time":144128,"text":"some hundreds of scientific\narticles on the Internet,"},{"time":146717,"text":"and we drafted a research proposal"},{"time":148989,"text":"in the beginning of our grade 12 year."},{"time":151237,"text":"We aimed to find bacteria\nfrom our local Fraser River"},{"time":154495,"text":"that can degrade a harmful\nplasticizer called phthalates."},{"time":158086,"text":"Phthalates are additives used\nin everyday plastic products"},{"time":160872,"text":"to increase their flexibility,\ndurability and transparency."},{"time":165305,"text":"Although they're part of the plastic,"},{"time":167237,"text":"they're not covalently bonded\nto the plastic backbone."},{"time":169889,"text":"As a result, they easily\nescape into our environment."},{"time":172869,"text":"Not only do phthalates\npollute our environment,"},{"time":175503,"text":"but they also pollute our bodies."},{"time":177436,"text":"To make the matter worse,\nphthalates are found in products"},{"time":180442,"text":"to which we have a high\nexposure, such as babies' toys,"},{"time":184218,"text":"beverage containers, cosmetics,\nand even food wraps."},{"time":188708,"text":"Phthalates are horrible because"},{"time":190564,"text":"they're so easily taken into our bodies."},{"time":192689,"text":"They can be absorbed by skin\ncontact, ingested, and inhaled."},{"time":197027,"text":"JY: Every year, at least 470\nmillion pounds of phthalates"},{"time":200939,"text":"contaminate our air, water and soil."},{"time":204328,"text":"The Environmental Protection Agency"},{"time":206019,"text":"even classified this group\nas a top-priority pollutant"},{"time":208980,"text":"because it's been shown to cause\ncancer and birth defects"},{"time":212036,"text":"by acting as a hormone disruptor."},{"time":214432,"text":"We read that each year,\nthe Vancouver municipal government"},{"time":217218,"text":"monitors phthalate\nconcentration levels in rivers"},{"time":219630,"text":"to assess their safety."},{"time":221380,"text":"So we figured, if there\nare places along our Fraser River"},{"time":224690,"text":"that are contaminated with phthalates,"},{"time":226773,"text":"and if there are bacteria\nthat are able to live in these areas,"},{"time":229987,"text":"then perhaps, perhaps these\nbacteria could have evolved"},{"time":233893,"text":"to break down phthalates."},{"time":235989,"text":"MW: So we presented this good idea"},{"time":238061,"text":"to Dr. Lindsay Eltis at the University\nof British Columbia,"},{"time":241052,"text":"and surprisingly, he actually\ntook us into his lab"},{"time":244272,"text":"and asked his graduate students\nAdam and James to help us."},{"time":248537,"text":"Little did we know at that time"},{"time":250246,"text":"that a trip to the dump\nand some research on the Internet"},{"time":253831,"text":"and plucking up the courage\nto act upon inspiration"},{"time":256324,"text":"would take us on a life-changing journey"},{"time":258716,"text":"of accidents and discoveries."},{"time":261124,"text":"JY: The first step in our project"},{"time":263186,"text":"was to collect soil samples\nfrom three different sites"},{"time":265782,"text":"along the Fraser River."},{"time":267254,"text":"Out of thousands of bacteria,\nwe wanted to find ones"},{"time":270127,"text":"that could break down phthalates,"},{"time":271449,"text":"so we enriched our cultures\nwith phthalates"},{"time":273608,"text":"as the only carbon source."},{"time":275256,"text":"This implied that, if anything\ngrew in our cultures,"},{"time":277757,"text":"then they must be able\nto live off of phthalates."},{"time":280210,"text":"Everything went well from there,"},{"time":282100,"text":"and we became amazing scientists.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":285253,"text":"MW: Um... uh, Jeanny. JY: I'm just joking."},{"time":288121,"text":"MW: Okay. Well, it was partially my fault."},{"time":290816,"text":"You see, I accidentally cracked the flask"},{"time":293986,"text":"that had contained our third\nenrichment culture,"},{"time":295767,"text":"and as a result, we had to wipe\ndown the incubator room"},{"time":298612,"text":"with bleach and ethanol twice."},{"time":300316,"text":"And this is only one of the examples\nof the many accidents"},{"time":303102,"text":"that happened during our experimentation."},{"time":305327,"text":"But this mistake turned\nout to be rather serendipitous."},{"time":308827,"text":"We noticed that the unharmed cultures"},{"time":311043,"text":"came from places\nof opposite contamination levels,"},{"time":314243,"text":"so this mistake actually\nled us to think that"},{"time":316775,"text":"perhaps we can compare"},{"time":318435,"text":"the different degradative\npotentials of bacteria"},{"time":321187,"text":"from sites\nof opposite contamination levels."},{"time":325158,"text":"JY: Now that we grew the bacteria,"},{"time":327084,"text":"we wanted to isolate strains\nby streaking onto mediate plates,"},{"time":330420,"text":"because we thought that would be"},{"time":332276,"text":"less accident-prone,\nbut we were wrong again."},{"time":335764,"text":"We poked holes in our agar while streaking"},{"time":339597,"text":"and contaminated some samples and funghi."},{"time":341866,"text":"As a result, we had to streak\nand restreak several times."},{"time":344605,"text":"Then we monitored phthalate utilization"},{"time":347273,"text":"and bacterial growth,"},{"time":349095,"text":"and found that they shared\nan inverse correlation,"},{"time":351735,"text":"so as bacterial populations increased,"},{"time":354322,"text":"phthalate concentrations decreased."},{"time":356160,"text":"This means that our bacteria were\nactually living off of phthalates."},{"time":360192,"text":"MW: So now that we found bacteria\nthat could break down phthalates,"},{"time":363407,"text":"we wondered what these bacteria were."},{"time":365699,"text":"So Jeanny and I took\nthree of our most efficient strains"},{"time":368390,"text":"and then performed gene\namplification sequencing on them"},{"time":371147,"text":"and matched our data with an online\ncomprehensive database."},{"time":374275,"text":"We were happy to see that,"},{"time":375948,"text":"although our three strains had\nbeen previously identified bacteria,"},{"time":379564,"text":"two of them were not previously associated"},{"time":382587,"text":"with phthalate degradation, so this\nwas actually a novel discovery."},{"time":386621,"text":"JY: To better understand\nhow this biodegradation works,"},{"time":390674,"text":"we wanted to verify the catabolic\npathways of our three strains."},{"time":394326,"text":"To do this, we extracted\nenzymes from our bacteria"},{"time":397238,"text":"and reacted with an intermediate\nof phthalic acid."},{"time":400806,"text":"MW: We monitored this experiment\nwith spectrophotometry"},{"time":403958,"text":"and obtained this beautiful graph."},{"time":406203,"text":"This graph shows\nthat our bacteria really do have"},{"time":408613,"text":"a genetic pathway\nto biodegrade phthalates."},{"time":411251,"text":"Our bacteria can transform phthalates,\nwhich is a harmful toxin,"},{"time":414613,"text":"into end products such\nas carbon dioxide, water"},{"time":417021,"text":"and alcohol."},{"time":418260,"text":"I know some of you\nin the crowd are thinking,"},{"time":420427,"text":"well, carbon dioxide is horrible,\nit's a greenhouse gas."},{"time":423282,"text":"But if our bacteria did not\nevolve to break down phthalates,"},{"time":426576,"text":"they would have used some other\nkind of carbon source,"},{"time":429172,"text":"and aerobic respiration would have led it"},{"time":431235,"text":"to have end products such\nas carbon dioxide anyway."},{"time":434547,"text":"We were also interested to see that,"},{"time":436849,"text":"although we've obtained greater diversity"},{"time":439008,"text":"of bacteria biodegraders\nfrom the bird habitat site,"},{"time":441978,"text":"we obtained the most efficient\ndegraders from the landfill site."},{"time":445050,"text":"So this fully shows that nature evolves"},{"time":447431,"text":"through natural selection."},{"time":450672,"text":"JY: So Miranda and I shared this research"},{"time":452769,"text":"at the Sanofi BioGENEius Challenge\ncompetition and were recognized"},{"time":455948,"text":"with the greatest\ncommercialization potential."},{"time":458984,"text":"Although we're not the first\nones to find bacteria"},{"time":461120,"text":"that can break down phthalates,"},{"time":462621,"text":"we were the first ones\nto look into our local river"},{"time":465119,"text":"and find a possible solution\nto a local problem."},{"time":468831,"text":"We have not only shown that bacteria"},{"time":471132,"text":"can be the solution to plastic\npollution, but also that"},{"time":474544,"text":"being open to uncertain\noutcomes and taking risks"},{"time":477845,"text":"create opportunities\nfor unexpected discoveries."},{"time":481120,"text":"Throughout this journey, we have also\ndiscovered our passion for science,"},{"time":484621,"text":"and are currently continuing research"},{"time":486463,"text":"on other fossil fuel\nchemicals in university."},{"time":489954,"text":"We hope that in the near future,"},{"time":491502,"text":"we'll be able to create model organisms"},{"time":493905,"text":"that can break down not only phthalates"},{"time":495787,"text":"but a wide variety\nof different contaminants."},{"time":499456,"text":"We can apply this to wastewater\ntreatment plants"},{"time":502152,"text":"to clean up our rivers"},{"time":503640,"text":"and other natural resources."},{"time":505976,"text":"And perhaps one day\nwe'll be able to tackle"},{"time":508515,"text":"the problem of solid plastic waste."},{"time":512553,"text":"MW: I think our journey\nhas truly transformed"},{"time":514888,"text":"our view of microorganisms,"},{"time":516953,"text":"and Jeanny and I have shown that"},{"time":518501,"text":"even mistakes can lead to discoveries."},{"time":520644,"text":"Einstein once said,"},{"time":521934,"text":"\"You can't solve problems\nby using the same kind"},{"time":524321,"text":"of thinking you used\nwhen you created them.\""},{"time":527589,"text":"If we're making plastic\nsynthetically, then we think"},{"time":530582,"text":"the solution would be to break\nthem down biochemically."},{"time":534556,"text":"Thank you. JY: Thank you."},{"time":536500,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}